Test 11

Here the idea is to rotate the magnetic field towards the axis at different rates and for many different magnetic fields.
I made for for simulations of seconds respectively.

This plot shows the vertices counts of the last frame of the simulations for all and many fields. Qualitatively we can see the same behavior but at different magnitudes.
From here I notices that the highest fraction of is found at around 5mT with the highest , which kind of gave me hope to make the alternating GS system.


For reference I graphed the time series of the vertices with the fastest to see how it behaves

Almost perfect, here ~95% of the vertices are of . I also ran simulations at faster but the situation did not improve.
At very fast the system did not order properly and at the end of the simulation there was mostly disorder. And for it did not change that much. So I don't expect this thing to fully decay into the GS.

In summary, I have no idea on what to do with this information.
